        <name>23.4.2.3 FS expression 3</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
Obtain the Fourier series of \[ f(t) = t  \hspace{1cm} \pi \leq t \leq \pi \hspace{1cm} f(t + 2\pi) = f(t) \] and use it to find the answer to \( 1 - \dfrac{1}{3} + \dfrac{1}{5} - \dfrac{1}{7} + \dots\)&lt;p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
\( 1 - \dfrac{1}{3} + \dfrac{1}{5} - \dfrac{1}{7} + \dots = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>As \( f(t) \) is an odd function, \( a_n = 0 \). For \( b_n\) we have
\[
\begin{align}
b_n &amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi}  \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^\pi }  t \sin nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi} \left( \left[ -\dfrac{t}{n} \cos nt \right]_{-\pi}^\pi + \dfrac{1}{n} \displaystyle{ \int _{-\pi}^\pi }  \cos nt \hspace{0.1cm} dt  \right) \\
&amp;amp;= \dfrac{1}{\pi} \left( -\dfrac{\pi}{n} \cos n \pi -\dfrac{\pi}{n} \cos n \pi + \dfrac{1}{n^2} \left[ \sin n\pi \right] _{-\pi}^\pi \right) \\
&amp;amp;= -\dfrac{2\cos n \pi}{n} 
\end{align}
\]
\[ =
\begin{cases}
-\dfrac{2}{n} \hspace{1cm} n = 2, 4, 6, \dots \\
\dfrac{2}{ni} \hspace{1cm} n = 1, 3, 5, \dots
\end{cases}
\]
which can be expressed as \( \dfrac{-2(-1)^n}{n} \).
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
So the Fourier series is given by
\[ f(t) =-2 \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{(-1)^n}{n} \sin nt  \]
Now setting \(t = \dfrac{\pi}{2} \) we have \(f(t) = \dfrac{\pi}{2}\). The Fourier series is
\[ -2 \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{(-1)^n}{n} \sin \dfrac{n\pi}{2} \]
which is equal to zero for even values of \(n\). Thus we have
which can be rearranged to give
\[ 
\begin{align}
\dfrac{\pi}{2} &amp;amp;= -2 \sum _{n=1}^\infty \dfrac{(-1)^n}{n}\sin \dfrac{n\pi}{2} \\
&amp;amp;= 2 \left( 1 - \dfrac{1}{3} + \dfrac{1}{5} - \dfrac{1}{7} + \dots \right) 
\end{align}
\]
Thus 
\[ 1 - \dfrac{1}{3} + \dfrac{1}{5} - \dfrac{1}{7} + \dots&amp;nbsp; = \dfrac{\pi}{4} \]</generalfeedback>
